am War, political history, or of social policy. Contemporary lawmakers should heed its historical lessons on how we ought to treat our returning veterans. Indeed, veterans wishing to fully understand their own homecoming experience will find great interest in the book's conclusions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aVeteransxEducationxHistoryxUnited States. 0aVeteransxEducationxLaw and legislationxHistoryxUnited States. 0aVeteransxEducationxLaw and legislationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aVeteransxEducationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xVeteransxEconomic conditionsxUnited States. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xVeteransxHistoryxUnited States. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xVeteransxSocial conditionsxUnited States. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xVeteranszUnited StatesxEconomic conditions. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xVeteranszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xVeteranszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 7aHISTORY / Military / Vietnam War.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071187540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814760420423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814760420.jpg  a978-3-11-071187-5  NYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK